tool.name: FillNoData

param.name: workspace
param.dialogReference: File-type workspace where the filled grid will be output.
param.pythonReference: File-type workspace where the filled grid will be output.

param.name: InGrid
param.dialogReference: Name of the grid to be filled. This grid must be in the workspace specified above.
param.pythonReference: Name of the grid to be filled. This grid must be in the workspace specified above.

param.name: OutGrid
param.dialogReference: Output grid name to be produced in the workspace specified above.
param.pythonReference: Output grid name to be produced in the workspace specified above.

tool.summary: Replaces NODATA values in a grid with mean values within 3x3 window. May be run repeatedly to fill in areas wider than 2 cells. Note the output is floating point, even if the input is integer. Note this will expand the data area of the grid around the outer edges of data, in addition to filling in NODATA gaps in the interior of the grid.
